nk Kit) and services (broadband), the transaction price is allocated to each distinct obligation based on its standalone selling price.\n\n### **3. AI Segment**\n*   *Note:* While the AI segment (AI Solutions & Infrastructure) is listed in the revenue disaggregation tables and is noted as a future recipient of launch capacity allocations, the provided text **does not detail** the specific revenue recognition policy for the AI segment.\n\n---\n\n### **Summary: When does SpaceX recognize revenue for these specific services?**\n*   **Launch Services:** Revenue is recognized at a **point in time**, specifically **upon the successful launch or deployment** of the customer's spacecraft/payload to its intended orbit. \n*   **Connectivity Services:** Revenue is recognized **over time**, continuously as the customer uses the service. It is recognized either **ratably over the subscription term** (for fixed monthly fees) or **based on actual data consumption** (for variable-priced services).",
