om month-to-month up to two years) as the customer consumes and benefits from the data. (Note: Historical IP may be satisfied at a single point in time, while future IP is satisfied over time).\n    *   *Multiple Performance Obligations:* If an arrangement contains multiple obligations, revenue is allocated on a relative basis using directly observable standalone selling prices, and recognized as each specific performance obligation is satisfied.\n*   **API Access to Grok Models:**\n    *   *Stand-Ready Access:* Revenue is recognized **ratably** over the contract term (typically month-to-month or up to one year).\n    *   *Usage-Based Arrangements:* Revenue is recognized **as services are consumed** by the customer.",
