criptions:** More satellites → better coverage/capacity → more subscribers and higher ARPU. Revenue recognized **over time** — ratably over the subscription period or based on data consumption.\n- **Hardware/Product sales (Starlink kits):** Revenue recognized at a **point in time** upon delivery (or installation for enterprise).\n- **Starshield (government networks):** Revenue recognized **over time** using the cost-to-cost method on multi-year fixed-price contracts.\n- **Starlink Mobile (satellite-to-mobile):** Revenue recognized **over time** as services are consumed.\n\nThe filing notes that next-generation V3 satellites (deployable via Starship) will deliver a **twenty-fold increase in downlink capacity** per launch versus Falcon 9, meaning each incremental kilogram of V3 satellite mass to orbit will generate substantially more connectivity revenue than current-generation satellites.\n\n### 3. AI Segment — Emerging Orbital Infrastructure Link\n\nThe AI segment (xAI, Grok, X platform) currently generates revenue primarily through:\n- **Advertising (X platform):** Recognized when ads are delivered and user engagement criteria are met (point in time).\n- **AI subscriptions & API access:** Recognized **ratably** over the subscription term or **as consumed** for usage-based arrangements.\n- **Data licensing:** Recognized **ratably** over the contract term.\n\nThe filing describes a forward-looking plan to deploy **orbital AI compute infrastructure** using Starship\'s massive payload capacity. If realized, incremental kilograms to orbit would directly enable AI segment compute capacity, though this remains a **forward-looking statement** and is not yet reflected in historical financials.\n\n---\n\n## Connectivity-to-Space Revenue Ratio Calculation\n\n| Period | Connectivity Revenue | Space Revenue | Ratio (Connectivity / Space) |\n|--------|---------------------|---------------|------------------------------|\n| **FY2025** | $11,387M | $4,086M | **2.79x** |\n| **Q1 20