tions as a cost center that enables the far larger and faster-growing Connectivity revenue stream. The Space segment\'s true economic value is not captured in its own revenue line but is instead embedded in the Connectivity segment\'s recurring subscription base.\n\n---\n\n**Note on recast financials:** All segment figures reflect the retrospectively recast consolidated entity under common-control accounting, including xAI (merged February 2, 2026) and X Holdings (merged into xAI March 28, 2025) for all historical periods presented. No period reflects standalone SpaceX operations exclusively.\n\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (Filed May 20, 2026)"\n    }\n  ]\n}',
